Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Rabies can occur in any mammal of any age. There are few animals that seem more resistant, but the raccoon does not fall into that category. Rabies is common in raccoons, skunks, and in some areas, coyotes and foxes.

Protection for yourself and your pets is important and vaccinating your pets provides such protection.

Most rabies exposures are posted in the ProMED-mail rabies update series, but with 18 people exposed, it was deemed reasonable to post this now. This is a large number of people and demonstrates how easily people can become exposed to such a "wildlife" pet.

Rhode Island may be found on the HealthMap/ProMED-Mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/7dtn. - Mod.TG]
